description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Trainee Associate Plaster Practitioner in our Fracture Clinic at the William Harvey Hospital in Ashford.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role will be working clinically as a member of the Plaster team. The successful post holder will be keen to develop basic competencies in casting and will be prepared to undertake extensive training for at least 1 year to develop enhanced competencies &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This will lead to undertaking a formal nationally recognised 6 week residential course in casting at Stanmore Orthopaedic Hospital in London fully funded.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful applicant will have a Healthcare Assistant, Technician or Associate Practitioner background. Existing Band 2/3 will undertake training as a Band 3 and qualify as a Band 4. Existing AP&#39;s will undertake training as a Band 4.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name:Alli Smith&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title:Fracture Clinic Service Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address:alli.smith@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number:07817085900&lt;/p&gt;
